CLYDE-MALLORY LINES, Appellee, v. DELAWARE, LACKAWANNA & WESTERN RAILROAD COMPANY, Appellant. (Consolidated Cause.) No. 243. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Feb. 4, 1935. John E. Morrissey, of New York City, for appellant. Burlingham; Veeder, Clark & Hupper, of New York City (Chauncey I. Clark and Frederic Conger, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before MANTON, L. HAND, and SWAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed.
